code-item.code:
template <class Handler>
  unspecified
    make_empty_physical_line_aware(Handler&& handler) noexcept(see below);
template <class Handler>
  unspecified
    make_empty_physical_line_aware(const std::reference_wrapper<Handler>& handler) noexcept;

code-item.returns:
An object of an unspecified type whose type meets the TextHandler requirements and that holds an object h where h is a copy of handler (first overload) or a reference to handler.get() (second overload). It forwards calls of its member functions to h; except that when its empty_physical_line member function is called with an argument where, it first calls h.start_record(where), and if its contexually converted return value to bool is not false, next calls h.end_record(where). Its return type and the return value are as follows:
if both of the return types of h.start_record(where) and h.end_record(where) are void, the return type shall be void,
otherwise, the return type shall be bool and the return type shall be false unless both of the the return values contextually converted to bool of h.start_record(where) and h.end_record(where) are not false.

