tr.td:
Called when the corresponding field has been skipped, that is, the record has had too few fields to reach the field.
                If r.get() is not nullptr where r is the return value, the translated value of the field shall be constructed from std::move(*r);
                otherwise, no values shall be put to the FieldTranslatorSink object ().

Called when the corresponding field has a value that can not be converted a value of T due to a format error.
                If r.get() is not nullptr where r is the return value, the translated value of the field shall be constructed from std::move(*r);
                otherwise, no values shall be put to the FieldTranslatorSink object ().

Called when the corresponding field has a value that is empty.
                If r.get() is not nullptr where r is the return value, the translated value of the field shall be constructed from std::move(*r);
                otherwise, no values shall be put to the FieldTranslatorSink object ().

